Doc: A partial derivative multiplied by a weighting factor.

Source.Contents:
/#
   A partial derivative multiplied by a weighting factor.
 #/
record FpML5.recordkeeping.WeightedPartialDerivative {
  # A reference to a partial derivative defined in the ComputedDerivative.model, i.e. defined as part of this sensitivity definition.
  partialDerivativeReference : FpML5.recordkeeping.PricingParameterDerivativeReference?

  # The weight factor to be applied to the partial derivative, e.g. 1 or -1, or some other scaling value.
  weight : decimal?

}

partialDerivativeReference.Doc: A reference to a partial derivative defined in the ComputedDerivative.model, i.e. defined as part of this sensitivity definition.
partialDerivativeReference.Name: partialDerivativeReference

weight.Doc: The weight factor to be applied to the partial derivative, e.g. 1 or -1, or some other scaling value.
weight.Name: weight
